text: Puts risk parity strategies in jeopardy they must delever
$TXN beat should buoy $INTC and $MU

When in a bad market and stocks have been going down, when they miss estimates and don't go down or go up the pundits say "it's in the stock, we know near the bottom and close to end of cuts, time to start buying".

So when we have had a 9 year straight up cycle, stocks up multiples from bottom, margins well above normalized levels, and the stocks trade down on estimate beats and raises, why do the same pundits say "I don't understand why they are not going up?"
